WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.000
Last week, we were in Ephesians 4 and we saw there that life is designed to be lived together in community.

2
00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:17.000
That's the kind of life that is offered to us in Jesus and that is experienced in the life of the church as we learn to follow him together.

3
00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:23.000
So you're right, church isn't an event. It's a family. We need each other.

4
00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:28.000
And let me just say, Lauren, I'm thrilled that you're part of this church family.

5
00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:31.000
We're all the better for it.

6
00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:35.000
Well, let's return to Ephesians chapter 4 this morning.

7
00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:44.000
As we come again to Ephesians chapter 4, we're going to see that the way of Christ is not just a life that is lived together.

8
00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:49.000
We're also going to see that it's a new kind of life altogether.

9
00:00:49.000 --> 00:00:53.000
It's a life that's different to the world around us.

10
00:00:53.000 --> 00:01:05.000
When you put your faith in Jesus and his saving work, you are given a new self, a new you, one that is different to the old you.

11
00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:10.000
We read about this beginning in verse 17.

12
00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:15.000
So let's listen carefully for these are the words of God.

13
00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:24.000
It says, Now this I say and testify in the Lord that you must no longer walk as the Gentiles do in the futility of their minds.

14
00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:35.000
They are darkened in their understanding, alienated from the life of God because of the ignorance that is in them due to their hardness of heart.

15
00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:43.000
They have become callous and have given themselves up to sensuality, greedy to practice every kind of impurity.

16
00:01:43.000 --> 00:01:46.000
But that is not the way you learned Christ.

17
00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:58.000
Assuming that you have heard about him and were taught in him as the truth is in Jesus to put off your old self, which belongs to your former manner of life.

18
00:01:58.000 --> 00:02:12.000
And is corrupt through deceitful desires and to be renewed in the spirit of your minds and to put on the new self created after the likeness of God in true righteousness and holiness.

19
00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:17.000
This is the word of the Lord. Let's pray.

20
00:02:17.000 --> 00:02:30.000
So Father, now as we come to your word, I pray that your spirit would open our eyes that we might behold your glory revealed to us in the face of Jesus.

21
00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:36.000
And as we do, I pray that we would be changed into his image from glory to glory.

22
00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:39.000
We pray all this in his name. Amen.

23
00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:45.000
Well, before we walk through this passage together in Ephesians 4, I'd like to share a quote with you.

24
00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:48.000
And it's from the Incredibles.

25
00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:53.000
The Pixar classic. Last week we looked at the Lion King together. So this week we're going to the Incredibles.

26
00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:58.000
But if you've seen it, you'll know that there's this superhero, Mr. Incredible.

27
00:02:58.000 --> 00:03:03.000
And there's also this little boy who really looks up to the superhero.

28
00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:08.000
And he really wants to be like him and he's called himself, do you remember his name?

29
00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:10.000
Incrediboy.

30
00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:13.000
And Incrediboy wants to grow up to be like Mr. Incredible.

31
00:03:13.000 --> 00:03:16.000
But he's got this propensity towards evil as well.

32
00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:20.000
And one day he is going to grow up as to become a villain.

33
00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:25.000
But you get a kind of glimpse into his darker side when he says something that's pretty profound.

34
00:03:25.000 --> 00:03:27.000
He asked Mr. Incredible a question.

35
00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:28.000
He says this.

36
00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:30.000
He said,

37
00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:38.000
It's interesting.

38
00:03:38.000 --> 00:03:42.000
You always say to be true to yourself. We hear that all the time in society, don't we?

39
00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:43.000
He says,

40
00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:50.000
Well, this morning, Scripture is putting before us two selves.

41
00:03:50.000 --> 00:03:53.000
An old self and a new self.

42
00:03:53.000 --> 00:03:57.000
And the question is, which of these selves will we be true to?

43
00:03:57.000 --> 00:04:02.000
Are we going to live according to the old self and follow the ways of the world?

44
00:04:02.000 --> 00:04:08.000
Or are we going to live according to the new self and follow Christ?

45
00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:13.000
And Paul reminds the Ephesians of the difference between the old self and the new self.

46
00:04:13.000 --> 00:04:20.000
And he calls on them to live in light of the new self that they have been given in Christ.

47
00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:26.000
And so he does so first of all by showing that the new self is different to the old self.

48
00:04:26.000 --> 00:04:27.000
It's different.

49
00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:30.000
So look at it with me together beginning in verse 17.

50
00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:31.000
He says,

51
00:04:38.000 --> 00:04:39.000
All right.

52
00:04:39.000 --> 00:04:45.000
So we saw last week that the first half of the book of Ephesians is all about what we believe.

53
00:04:45.000 --> 00:04:51.000
And the second half is all about how we live as a result of what we believe.

54
00:04:51.000 --> 00:04:54.000
And the word that's used for how we live is our walk.

55
00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:56.000
That's a continuous way of life.

56
00:04:56.000 --> 00:04:59.000
But notice what Paul says about our walk in verse 17.

57
00:04:59.000 --> 00:05:04.000
He talks about how we're no longer to walk or to live as the Gentiles.

58
00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:07.000
Now that's an unusual way of speaking.

59
00:05:07.000 --> 00:05:09.000
It's probably striking to the people who first heard it too.

60
00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:12.000
Because remember, the church is made up of both Jews and Gentiles alike.

61
00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:19.000
Gentiles is just another way of saying people who are not Jewish from other ethnic groups.

62
00:05:19.000 --> 00:05:22.000
So Gentiles don't live like Gentiles.

63
00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:23.000
Kind of confusing.

64
00:05:23.000 --> 00:05:24.000
What's he talking about?

65
00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:30.000
Well, in the Old Testament, God set apart the people of Israel for himself.

66
00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:34.000
And when he did so, he told them they were called to be his holy people.

67
00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:39.000
And they were to live in ways that reflected that.

68
00:05:39.000 --> 00:05:42.000
And he also put the same thing forward negatively.

69
00:05:42.000 --> 00:05:43.000
He says,

70
00:05:49.000 --> 00:05:53.000
Paul picks up on that language and applies it to the church.

71
00:05:53.000 --> 00:05:58.000
So back in chapter one, the book opened by telling us that we were chosen in Christ

72
00:05:58.000 --> 00:06:00.000
that we might be holy.

73
00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:01.000
Right?

74
00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:02.000
The same as God's chosen people before.

75
00:06:02.000 --> 00:06:04.000
We are to be holy.

76
00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:07.000
So here's the bottom line of what Paul is saying.

77
00:06:07.000 --> 00:06:11.000
He's saying the church is to be different to the world.

78
00:06:11.000 --> 00:06:15.000
And he's saying that the church is to be different to the world.

79
00:06:15.000 --> 00:06:19.000
He's saying the church is to be different to the world.

80
00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:20.000
Period.

81
00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:25.000
The way we live our lives should have a distinct quality to it.

82
00:06:25.000 --> 00:06:32.000
We must not walk as the Gentiles, as the world around us, the culture we're in is walking.

83
00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:36.000
One of the ways that crimes are investigated is forensics.

84
00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:40.000
And I don't know how investigators do what they do, but it's amazing.

85
00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:45.000
They might be investigating a crime and they look at DNA

86
00:06:45.000 --> 00:06:49.000
or they look at different evidence that is there at the crime scene.

87
00:06:49.000 --> 00:06:55.000
But another method that's sometimes used is something called forensic gate analysis.

88
00:06:55.000 --> 00:06:57.000
Forensic gate analysis.

89
00:06:57.000 --> 00:06:58.000
So what's that all about?

90
00:06:58.000 --> 00:07:03.000
Well, even if somebody, say they commit a crime and there's a security camera,

91
00:07:03.000 --> 00:07:05.000
but their face isn't in view.

92
00:07:05.000 --> 00:07:06.000
Say they're wearing a mask.

93
00:07:06.000 --> 00:07:09.000
Well, what can happen is the way they walk,

94
00:07:09.000 --> 00:07:14.000
their distinct way of walking can be used to discover who the criminal is

95
00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:19.000
by matching their walk with the person who was caught in the act on the security camera.

96
00:07:19.000 --> 00:07:25.000
So they're analyzing their walk to identify the suspect.

97
00:07:25.000 --> 00:07:29.000
We live in a cultural context where many profess to be Christians,

98
00:07:29.000 --> 00:07:33.000
but they are betrayed by their walk.

99
00:07:33.000 --> 00:07:35.000
So they identify as a Christian.

100
00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:42.000
They may have even made a decision in a church or something in the past to accept Jesus.

101
00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:49.000
But there's nothing in their life today that would indicate that they are actually following Christ.

102
00:07:49.000 --> 00:07:53.000
They're just drifting along with the cultural current of Christianity

103
00:07:53.000 --> 00:07:59.000
as though everything is absolutely fine because our culture tells us it's fine to identify as a Christian.

104
00:07:59.000 --> 00:08:04.000
But to continue to live however you want to live, you do you, right?

105
00:08:04.000 --> 00:08:08.000
But here's what Jesus said in Matthew chapter seven.

106
00:08:08.000 --> 00:08:14.000
He said, Not everyone who says to me, Lord, Lord will enter the kingdom of heaven.

107
00:08:14.000 --> 00:08:19.000
But the one who does the will of my father who was in heaven.

108
00:08:19.000 --> 00:08:23.000
On that day, many will say to me, Lord, do we not prophesy in your name

109
00:08:23.000 --> 00:08:27.000
and cast out demons in your name and do many mighty works in your name.

110
00:08:27.000 --> 00:08:31.000
And then I will declare to them, I never knew you,

111
00:08:31.000 --> 00:08:36.000
depart from me, you workers of lawlessness.

112
00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:41.000
Now for some people, you know, they might genuinely know the Lord

113
00:08:41.000 --> 00:08:45.000
and just that it's just that they have a lot of room to grow.

114
00:08:45.000 --> 00:08:51.000
But I fear that for many, they are actually worshipping a false Christ,

115
00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:54.000
a God that is made in their own image,

116
00:08:54.000 --> 00:08:58.000
that they've just kind of slapped the name Jesus on to rather than following

117
00:08:58.000 --> 00:09:02.000
the real Jesus that is revealed to us in Scripture.

118
00:09:02.000 --> 00:09:06.000
Because the way of Christ is different to the way of the world.

119
00:09:06.000 --> 00:09:08.000
So what is the way of the Gentiles exactly?

120
00:09:08.000 --> 00:09:11.000
What is that walk? What's so bad about it?

121
00:09:11.000 --> 00:09:15.000
Well, Paul goes on to describe the ways of the world and the bankruptcy of it.

122
00:09:15.000 --> 00:09:18.000
And just to forewarn you, he doesn't kind of pull any punches here.

123
00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:23.000
Like let me say a few nice things first and then slip in a little bit that's critical.

124
00:09:23.000 --> 00:09:28.000
But you know, if you're on a canoe heading towards a deadly waterfall that's going to kill you,

125
00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:32.000
you don't need compliments on your canoe of choice or the color it's paying after whatever.

126
00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:35.000
You need to be told of the imminent danger that you are in.

127
00:09:35.000 --> 00:09:39.000
So Paul shows the dire condition of the way of the world.

128
00:09:39.000 --> 00:09:43.000
He speaks about the futility of their minds.

129
00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:46.000
You see that at the end of verse 17.

130
00:09:46.000 --> 00:09:49.000
So the word futility means meaninglessness.

131
00:09:49.000 --> 00:09:53.000
So people are trying to figure out what life is all about on their own,

132
00:09:53.000 --> 00:09:55.000
but their search is coming up empty.

133
00:09:55.000 --> 00:09:57.000
They can't figure it out.

134
00:09:57.000 --> 00:09:59.000
It's like trying to find your way in the dark.

135
00:09:59.000 --> 00:10:01.000
And he speaks about darkness here.

136
00:10:01.000 --> 00:10:02.000
He speaks about ignorance.

137
00:10:02.000 --> 00:10:03.000
So it's good to reason.

138
00:10:03.000 --> 00:10:06.000
And we're invited to use our minds to reason things out.

139
00:10:06.000 --> 00:10:07.000
Of course.

140
00:10:07.000 --> 00:10:08.000
But here's the thing.

141
00:10:08.000 --> 00:10:10.000
You can have the highest IQ.

142
00:10:10.000 --> 00:10:13.000
You can study at the finest of schools.

143
00:10:13.000 --> 00:10:15.000
Read the best books that are out there.

144
00:10:15.000 --> 00:10:18.000
Listen to all the podcasts you want.

145
00:10:18.000 --> 00:10:23.000
But you can't reason your way into the purpose for which you were created.

146
00:10:23.000 --> 00:10:25.000
We can't figure that out on our own.

147
00:10:25.000 --> 00:10:29.000
Our minds alone cannot get us there.

148
00:10:31.000 --> 00:10:33.000
But he doesn't just speak about our thoughts.

149
00:10:33.000 --> 00:10:36.000
This kind of darkness of the mind.

150
00:10:36.000 --> 00:10:38.000
He also speaks about our desires.

151
00:10:38.000 --> 00:10:40.000
Our deceitful desires.

152
00:10:40.000 --> 00:10:46.000
So even though you give a lot of thought to the meaning of life,

153
00:10:46.000 --> 00:10:50.000
you've also got some desires that drive you.

154
00:10:50.000 --> 00:10:53.000
But even if you don't give a lot of thought to the meaning of life,

155
00:10:53.000 --> 00:10:55.000
you never think twice about it.

156
00:10:55.000 --> 00:10:57.000
You still want to feel good.

157
00:10:57.000 --> 00:10:59.000
So wherever you're at in your thinking this morning,

158
00:10:59.000 --> 00:11:00.000
we all want to feel good.

159
00:11:00.000 --> 00:11:03.000
So however rational we think we are,

160
00:11:03.000 --> 00:11:06.000
we are all to one degree or another

161
00:11:06.000 --> 00:11:10.000
following or tempted to follow after our desires.

162
00:11:10.000 --> 00:11:13.000
So there's an ignorance of God,

163
00:11:13.000 --> 00:11:16.000
but there's an also willful moving away from him

164
00:11:16.000 --> 00:11:20.000
and following after our selfish desires instead.

165
00:11:20.000 --> 00:11:26.000
And those selfish desires are seen in our actions, our practices.

166
00:11:26.000 --> 00:11:30.000
There's specific actions that are mentioned here.

167
00:11:30.000 --> 00:11:34.000
It talks about people giving themselves up to sensuality.

168
00:11:34.000 --> 00:11:39.000
So sensuality is often associated with sexual gratification.

169
00:11:39.000 --> 00:11:41.000
But then he goes on to talk about

170
00:11:41.000 --> 00:11:43.000
all kinds of impurities.

171
00:11:43.000 --> 00:11:44.000
So right after that he says,

172
00:11:44.000 --> 00:11:50.000
greedy to practice every kind of impurity.

173
00:11:50.000 --> 00:11:55.000
So it could be a life of unrestrained hedonism that you're drawn to,

174
00:11:55.000 --> 00:12:00.000
or it could be a more respectable version of following after your desire.

175
00:12:00.000 --> 00:12:05.000
But nevertheless, it's your own desires that is driving you forward.

176
00:12:05.000 --> 00:12:10.000
Any number of desires might be on the driver's seat of our hearts.

177
00:12:10.000 --> 00:12:13.000
It could be a desire for pleasure, it could be a desire for comfort,

178
00:12:13.000 --> 00:12:19.000
or a desire for security, or a desire for success or significance.

179
00:12:19.000 --> 00:12:22.000
And our actions then flow from those desires

180
00:12:22.000 --> 00:12:26.000
where we try to fulfill those desires on our own.

181
00:12:26.000 --> 00:12:29.000
Thinking that will fulfill us.

182
00:12:29.000 --> 00:12:36.000
But those desires are deceitful, we read in verse 22.

183
00:12:36.000 --> 00:12:37.000
Jeremiah 17-9 says,

184
00:12:37.000 --> 00:12:40.000
the heart is deceitful above all things and desperately wicked.

185
00:12:40.000 --> 00:12:42.000
Who can know it?

186
00:12:42.000 --> 00:12:46.000
One of the ways our desires deceive us is they over promise and under deliver.

187
00:12:46.000 --> 00:12:49.000
They promise fulfillment, but when we finally get them,

188
00:12:49.000 --> 00:12:55.000
they leave us still hungry for more, disappointed, unfulfilled.

189
00:12:55.000 --> 00:12:58.000
And then we start with those deceitful desires.

190
00:12:58.000 --> 00:13:02.000
We're just convincing ourselves that it's okay, that's just how life is.

191
00:13:02.000 --> 00:13:04.000
And so however rational we think we are,

192
00:13:04.000 --> 00:13:09.000
our desires lead us to convince ourselves that we're going in the right direction

193
00:13:09.000 --> 00:13:11.000
or that it doesn't really matter.

194
00:13:11.000 --> 00:13:14.000
Now initially, following after our selfish desires

195
00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:17.000
could give us a sense of guilt and shame.

196
00:13:17.000 --> 00:13:20.000
We're born with a conscience, a God-given conscience.

197
00:13:20.000 --> 00:13:23.000
And these desires being fulfilled is called impurity.

198
00:13:23.000 --> 00:13:27.000
We might feel the uncleanness when we commit these sins

199
00:13:27.000 --> 00:13:31.000
that are listed out for us in Ephesians.

200
00:13:31.000 --> 00:13:35.000
But something scary can happen over time

201
00:13:35.000 --> 00:13:39.000
is that we can develop a callous heart.

202
00:13:39.000 --> 00:13:44.000
So Paul talks about they have become callous in verse 19.

203
00:13:44.000 --> 00:13:48.000
He talks about the hardness of heart in verse 18.

204
00:13:48.000 --> 00:13:52.000
You can get to the place where you've rationalized,

205
00:13:52.000 --> 00:13:54.000
you follow after your desires,

206
00:13:54.000 --> 00:13:56.000
you've felt the pain and the shame of it in the past,

207
00:13:56.000 --> 00:13:58.000
but now you're numb to it.

208
00:13:58.000 --> 00:14:02.000
You're just at peace with the path you have chosen.

209
00:14:02.000 --> 00:14:06.000
I play the guitar, and there have been seasons

210
00:14:06.000 --> 00:14:08.000
where I've not played the guitar for a long time.

211
00:14:08.000 --> 00:14:12.000
If you've ever started guitar or you haven't played for a long time,

212
00:14:12.000 --> 00:14:15.000
you'll know that when you first start playing, it's painful.

213
00:14:15.000 --> 00:14:17.000
You're putting your fingers on the strings,

214
00:14:17.000 --> 00:14:18.000
you're pushing them down,

215
00:14:18.000 --> 00:14:20.000
and after you've played for a while, you really feel it

216
00:14:20.000 --> 00:14:24.000
because what has to happen is you've got to develop callouses over time

217
00:14:24.000 --> 00:14:26.000
so you no longer feel the pain.

218
00:14:26.000 --> 00:14:30.000
So that's what's going on here with this callousness, this hardness of heart.

219
00:14:30.000 --> 00:14:33.000
You once felt the pain, you don't feel it anymore.

220
00:14:33.000 --> 00:14:38.000
You've given yourself over to those desires.

221
00:14:38.000 --> 00:14:41.000
And now from your perspective, sin isn't the problem.

222
00:14:41.000 --> 00:14:46.000
The problem is those things that keep you from chasing after those desires.

223
00:14:46.000 --> 00:14:50.000
And still, that isn't the worst part.

224
00:14:50.000 --> 00:14:57.000
He speaks of being alienated from the life of God in verse 18.

225
00:14:57.000 --> 00:15:02.000
So the life that we were made for is a life with God.

226
00:15:02.000 --> 00:15:05.000
We were made to know Him, to enjoy Him.

227
00:15:05.000 --> 00:15:08.000
So apart from His light, we're left in darkness.

228
00:15:08.000 --> 00:15:14.000
And apart from His life, we are left with death.

229
00:15:14.000 --> 00:15:15.000
So this is the way of the world.

230
00:15:15.000 --> 00:15:16.000
This is where it leads.

231
00:15:16.000 --> 00:15:19.000
However attractive it looks at the time,

232
00:15:19.000 --> 00:15:23.000
that's what we're looking at in reality.

233
00:15:23.000 --> 00:15:26.000
But we're not just looking at the world here.

234
00:15:26.000 --> 00:15:30.000
This isn't just an out there problem for us to critique the culture.

235
00:15:30.000 --> 00:15:34.000
It's also an in here problem.

236
00:15:34.000 --> 00:15:41.000
It's there so we can all look at our own hearts and ask what way are we following.

237
00:15:41.000 --> 00:15:46.000
I don't know if you've ever come across Alexander Solzhenitsyn's, the Gulag Archipelago,

238
00:15:46.000 --> 00:15:52.000
in that he writes about being in Soviet labor camps and the awful atrocities

239
00:15:52.000 --> 00:15:58.000
that were committed at the time that he saw and experienced firsthand.

240
00:15:58.000 --> 00:16:04.000
But he warns about thinking that things like that happen just because there are exceptionally evil people out there

241
00:16:04.000 --> 00:16:07.000
in the world that are altogether different from the rest of us.

242
00:16:07.000 --> 00:16:10.000
Like I would never commit anything like that.

243
00:16:10.000 --> 00:16:11.000
And he writes this.

244
00:16:11.000 --> 00:16:14.000
He says, oh, if it were all so simple.

245
00:16:14.000 --> 00:16:22.000
If only there were evil people sometimes somewhere rather insidiously committing evil deeds

246
00:16:22.000 --> 00:16:28.000
and it were only necessary to separate them from the rest of us and destroy them.

247
00:16:28.000 --> 00:16:30.000
But then he says this really profound.

248
00:16:30.000 --> 00:16:40.000
He says, but the line dividing good and evil cuts through the heart of every human being.

249
00:16:40.000 --> 00:16:44.000
Who is willing to destroy his own heart?

250
00:16:44.000 --> 00:16:50.000
So this is here so that we can see the condition of our own hearts apart from Christ.

251
00:16:50.000 --> 00:16:52.000
He doesn't just speak about the way of the Gentiles.

252
00:16:52.000 --> 00:16:55.000
He speaks about the old self.

253
00:16:55.000 --> 00:16:58.000
So we have to ask ourselves the question.

254
00:16:58.000 --> 00:17:05.000
Am I still part of that world living according to my own thoughts, my own desires?

255
00:17:05.000 --> 00:17:09.000
Have I been deceiving myself?

256
00:17:09.000 --> 00:17:13.000
If so, what can be done?

257
00:17:13.000 --> 00:17:19.000
Well, the solution that's put before us here is this to put on the new self.

258
00:17:19.000 --> 00:17:21.000
There is an old self.

259
00:17:21.000 --> 00:17:23.000
It's following after the ways of the world.

260
00:17:23.000 --> 00:17:28.000
You put it off, but there is a new self that you're called to put on.

261
00:17:28.000 --> 00:17:29.000
So what does that mean?

262
00:17:29.000 --> 00:17:33.000
What's language that's used for changing clothes?

263
00:17:33.000 --> 00:17:39.000
Over the holidays, the boys and I went with their cousins to a laser tag place,

264
00:17:39.000 --> 00:17:40.000
but it wasn't indoors.

265
00:17:40.000 --> 00:17:42.000
It was all outdoors and it had been raining.

266
00:17:42.000 --> 00:17:44.000
So you can imagine how muddy it was when we got there.

267
00:17:44.000 --> 00:17:49.000
We actually had to sign a waiver before saying that we won't sue anybody if we get hurt.

268
00:17:49.000 --> 00:17:54.000
We also understand that our clothes may very well be completely ruined and written off.

269
00:17:54.000 --> 00:17:57.000
So it lived up to it.

270
00:17:57.000 --> 00:17:59.000
We all came back and we were extremely muddy.

271
00:17:59.000 --> 00:18:03.000
So the first thing we all needed to do was to get a new set of clothes.

272
00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:07.000
We needed to change clothes here and get rid of our old filthy ones.

273
00:18:07.000 --> 00:18:08.000
So that's the language used here.

274
00:18:08.000 --> 00:18:09.000
Put off, put on.

275
00:18:09.000 --> 00:18:11.000
It's language used for changing clothes.

276
00:18:11.000 --> 00:18:13.000
Our old self is utterly ruined.

277
00:18:13.000 --> 00:18:17.000
We need to put it off and put on the new self.

278
00:18:17.000 --> 00:18:20.000
But here's what he's not telling us to do.

279
00:18:20.000 --> 00:18:23.000
We might think, well, maybe he's telling us to stop doing the old stuff

280
00:18:23.000 --> 00:18:28.000
and start doing some new stuff, stop with the bad things,

281
00:18:28.000 --> 00:18:30.000
and start doing some good things.

282
00:18:30.000 --> 00:18:35.000
Like Christianity is, you know, you stop cussing and start praying or something like that.

283
00:18:35.000 --> 00:18:38.000
But he's not telling us that.

284
00:18:38.000 --> 00:18:41.000
He's not telling us to put off our old stuff merely.

285
00:18:41.000 --> 00:18:45.000
He's telling us to put off our old self.

286
00:18:45.000 --> 00:18:47.000
He's not telling us to put on new stuff.

287
00:18:47.000 --> 00:18:50.000
He's telling us to put on a new self entirely.

288
00:18:50.000 --> 00:18:56.000
So the problem with just adding some good things, some religious things to the old self

289
00:18:56.000 --> 00:18:58.000
is still the old self.

290
00:18:58.000 --> 00:19:01.000
It's like, imagine you haven't showered for years

291
00:19:01.000 --> 00:19:05.000
and all of a sudden you go and you change into a new shirt.

292
00:19:05.000 --> 00:19:07.000
That's really not going to change anything.

293
00:19:07.000 --> 00:19:11.000
The problem is much deeper than that.

294
00:19:11.000 --> 00:19:19.000
So our sin has so corrupted us that the kind of surface solution of behavior modification cannot work.

295
00:19:19.000 --> 00:19:23.000
We're alienated from the life of God, dead in our sins.

296
00:19:23.000 --> 00:19:28.000
It's not going to change us to the degree we need to be changed.

297
00:19:28.000 --> 00:19:31.000
You need an entirely new you.

298
00:19:31.000 --> 00:19:33.000
So where are you going to get that?

299
00:19:33.000 --> 00:19:36.000
Where is the new self found?

300
00:19:36.000 --> 00:19:38.000
Well, there's a hint here in verse 20.

301
00:19:38.000 --> 00:19:40.000
He tells the church, he says,

302
00:19:40.000 --> 00:19:46.000
but that is not the way you learned Christ.

303
00:19:46.000 --> 00:19:52.000
So those who have this new self are those who've learned Christ.

304
00:19:52.000 --> 00:19:57.000
The new self that we all need is offered to us in Jesus.

305
00:19:57.000 --> 00:20:00.000
So it's those who've learned Christ to have this new self.

306
00:20:00.000 --> 00:20:03.000
So have you learned Christ is one way of asking it.

307
00:20:03.000 --> 00:20:06.000
Jesus was a historical figure.

308
00:20:06.000 --> 00:20:12.000
You can look at both Christian sources and non-Christian sources that point to the fact that

309
00:20:12.000 --> 00:20:15.000
His existence is a historical reality.

310
00:20:15.000 --> 00:20:20.000
We have these eyewitness accounts for us recorded in scripture that were written in the time

311
00:20:20.000 --> 00:20:25.000
where people who had actually seen Jesus could attest to the truth of what was being written here.

312
00:20:25.000 --> 00:20:29.000
So we need to learn the facts about Jesus as a historical figure.

313
00:20:29.000 --> 00:20:34.000
But notice it doesn't say, but that's not the way you learned about Christ.

314
00:20:34.000 --> 00:20:38.000
He's not just talking about having learned facts about Jesus.

315
00:20:38.000 --> 00:20:42.000
He's talking about learning Him.

316
00:20:42.000 --> 00:20:45.000
So what's he saying there?

317
00:20:45.000 --> 00:20:48.000
Christ isn't just a historical figure.

318
00:20:48.000 --> 00:20:50.000
He is alive.

319
00:20:50.000 --> 00:20:52.000
He is reigning.

320
00:20:52.000 --> 00:20:56.000
He is actively at work in the world by His Spirit.

321
00:20:56.000 --> 00:21:01.000
So learning Christ is coming to know Christ Himself.

322
00:21:01.000 --> 00:21:05.000
So learning Christ means, yes, learning truth about Jesus,

323
00:21:05.000 --> 00:21:12.000
but it's also entering into a living relationship with Jesus.

324
00:21:12.000 --> 00:21:19.000
The new life that we are offered is a life that is vitally connected to His own.

325
00:21:19.000 --> 00:21:26.000
It is through Jesus that we are reunited with the life of God that we are alienated from.

326
00:21:26.000 --> 00:21:28.000
Like God is the source of life.

327
00:21:28.000 --> 00:21:29.000
How do we get back to that?

328
00:21:29.000 --> 00:21:32.000
Jesus reunites us with God.

329
00:21:32.000 --> 00:21:36.000
And so we're given this new life in Him.

330
00:21:36.000 --> 00:21:38.000
So what's that life like?

331
00:21:38.000 --> 00:21:42.000
This life that is given to us in Jesus.

332
00:21:42.000 --> 00:21:44.000
Well, when God created us, He created us.

333
00:21:44.000 --> 00:21:49.000
We're told in Genesis 1 in His likeness, in His image.

334
00:21:49.000 --> 00:21:54.000
Sin, as we've just read about, marred that image.

335
00:21:54.000 --> 00:21:59.000
There was devastating consequences in the world that we read about earlier.

336
00:21:59.000 --> 00:22:04.000
But when Jesus came into the world, He came as the perfect image of God.

337
00:22:04.000 --> 00:22:08.000
He came as a new and better atom, if you will,

338
00:22:08.000 --> 00:22:11.000
who perfectly reflects the likeness of God.

339
00:22:11.000 --> 00:22:18.000
His life was a life of perfect holiness and perfect righteousness.

340
00:22:18.000 --> 00:22:28.000
So in the person of Jesus, we see a new self, a new way of being, a new life.

341
00:22:28.000 --> 00:22:30.000
All right, so we have that.

342
00:22:30.000 --> 00:22:35.000
So the new self is a self that is made in the likeness of Jesus.

343
00:22:35.000 --> 00:22:41.000
So you have in your mind the old self, full of sin, following the ways of the world,

344
00:22:41.000 --> 00:22:46.000
the new self, true righteousness and holiness found in Jesus.

345
00:22:46.000 --> 00:22:50.000
Now take those thoughts and come with me to the cross.

346
00:22:50.000 --> 00:22:54.000
So what do we see happening at the cross?

347
00:22:54.000 --> 00:22:59.000
Here's what Paul says in 2 Corinthians chapter 5 in verse 21.

348
00:22:59.000 --> 00:23:05.000
There he who knew no sin became sin for us,

349
00:23:05.000 --> 00:23:11.000
that we might be made the righteousness of God in him.

350
00:23:11.000 --> 00:23:20.000
So on the cross, Jesus took upon himself our old self, our sin,

351
00:23:20.000 --> 00:23:24.000
all of its corruption and our death.

352
00:23:24.000 --> 00:23:30.000
In Romans 6, we're even told that there our old self is crucified with him.

353
00:23:30.000 --> 00:23:32.000
So he takes our sin.

354
00:23:32.000 --> 00:23:38.000
And here's what is offered to us in Jesus, is his perfect righteousness.

355
00:23:38.000 --> 00:23:44.000
So we're given this new life in Jesus and his perfection, his likeness.

356
00:23:44.000 --> 00:23:47.000
And so the choice is between the two.

357
00:23:47.000 --> 00:23:50.000
Am I going to hold on to my old sin?

358
00:23:50.000 --> 00:23:53.000
Or am I going to receive his righteousness?

359
00:23:53.000 --> 00:23:55.000
Am I going to pay the price for my sin?

360
00:23:55.000 --> 00:23:57.000
Or am I going to say, no, Jesus paid it.

361
00:23:57.000 --> 00:24:02.000
And I receive him in his life by faith.

362
00:24:02.000 --> 00:24:06.000
So these two selves are before us, the old self, the new self.

363
00:24:06.000 --> 00:24:09.000
The one that led to the crucifixion of Jesus.

364
00:24:09.000 --> 00:24:15.000
And the new self that comes through the resurrection of Jesus.

365
00:24:15.000 --> 00:24:20.000
So how do we choose between the two?

366
00:24:20.000 --> 00:24:24.000
What must be a deliberate choice?

367
00:24:24.000 --> 00:24:28.000
When Paul says in verse 22 and verse 23, put off and put on,

368
00:24:28.000 --> 00:24:33.000
it is in a very particular tense, the verb there.

369
00:24:33.000 --> 00:24:39.000
Basically what is happening there, it's a very definite action that has taken place in the past.

370
00:24:39.000 --> 00:24:44.000
So in other words, what he's saying when he says put off the old self and put on the new self,

371
00:24:44.000 --> 00:24:48.000
he's saying there was a time in the past when you learned Christ,

372
00:24:48.000 --> 00:24:50.000
when you heard about him and what he did for you,

373
00:24:50.000 --> 00:24:58.000
and you decided to renounce the old self and receive Jesus by faith.

374
00:24:58.000 --> 00:25:03.000
Now there will be some of you in here who can't look back to a particular time

375
00:25:03.000 --> 00:25:06.000
when you know that was the point in time when that happened for you,

376
00:25:06.000 --> 00:25:08.000
but you know it happened.

377
00:25:08.000 --> 00:25:13.000
You know the old self is gone and you have this new self, praised God.

378
00:25:13.000 --> 00:25:16.000
But you may be here and you're not sure.

379
00:25:16.000 --> 00:25:21.000
And this choice is laid before you, the choice of the old self and the new self.

380
00:25:21.000 --> 00:25:28.000
So will I reject Christ and hold on to my old life?

381
00:25:28.000 --> 00:25:34.000
Or will I embrace Jesus and the life that God offers me in him?

382
00:25:34.000 --> 00:25:37.000
So the choice is before all of us.

383
00:25:37.000 --> 00:25:44.000
And the call here is to put on the new self, to receive Christ by faith.

384
00:25:44.000 --> 00:25:51.000
But also we see that when we embrace Christ, there's that deliberate decision that's made to put off and put on.

385
00:25:51.000 --> 00:25:57.000
You see when we're doing that we're also embracing a new way of life that comes with knowing Jesus.

386
00:25:57.000 --> 00:26:03.000
Right, if he is living and present in our lives, he will change our lives.

387
00:26:03.000 --> 00:26:07.000
Now Paul is mainly writing to people who have put on the new self.

388
00:26:07.000 --> 00:26:13.000
So here's the main thrust of what he's writing here when he's reminding them of putting off the old self and putting on the new one.

389
00:26:13.000 --> 00:26:18.000
Here's what he's saying, you are a new creation, so live as a new creation.

390
00:26:18.000 --> 00:26:20.000
This is who you are.

391
00:26:20.000 --> 00:26:22.000
Now live in light of it.

392
00:26:22.000 --> 00:26:27.000
Be true to your new self, if you will.

393
00:26:27.000 --> 00:26:31.000
You know we've got some newlyweds that are part of the church here.

394
00:26:31.000 --> 00:26:36.000
And before you get married you are two individuals.

395
00:26:36.000 --> 00:26:39.000
And then when you get married you are made one.

396
00:26:39.000 --> 00:26:43.000
You are united together as husband and wife.

397
00:26:43.000 --> 00:26:51.000
But then, I tell you this 16 years on, it takes time to live together as one.

398
00:26:51.000 --> 00:27:00.000
Right, to be living in light of your marital union, this one life you have together.

399
00:27:00.000 --> 00:27:02.000
So it is with Christ.

400
00:27:02.000 --> 00:27:06.000
When you put your faith in him, you are united to him.

401
00:27:06.000 --> 00:27:09.000
And now you must learn to walk in step with him.

402
00:27:09.000 --> 00:27:12.000
And that is an ongoing process.

403
00:27:12.000 --> 00:27:20.000
But the wonderful news is that Christ himself is with you every step of the way by his spirit.

404
00:27:20.000 --> 00:27:25.000
He is the one who is changing us into his lightness.

405
00:27:25.000 --> 00:27:27.000
So what does that look like in practice?

406
00:27:27.000 --> 00:27:30.000
Well we are going to see that over the coming weeks.

407
00:27:30.000 --> 00:27:32.000
Paul is going to get very specific.

408
00:27:32.000 --> 00:27:39.000
But what he tells us here right at the start is that Jesus changes us from the inside out.

409
00:27:39.000 --> 00:27:46.000
We saw it with the ways of the world in our old selves that the problem was internal and that manifested in external ways.

410
00:27:46.000 --> 00:27:48.000
So the same thing is true in how Jesus changes us.

411
00:27:48.000 --> 00:27:52.000
He changes us from the inside out.

412
00:27:52.000 --> 00:27:55.000
So it begins with a renewing of our minds.

413
00:27:55.000 --> 00:28:00.000
It says in verse 23, to be renewed in the spirit of your minds.

414
00:28:00.000 --> 00:28:03.000
So we have to ask ourselves what is shaping my mind?

415
00:28:03.000 --> 00:28:07.000
Is it the culture or is it Christ?

416
00:28:07.000 --> 00:28:13.000
If I'm new in him, what am I allowing to shape my mind?

417
00:28:13.000 --> 00:28:22.000
So in Romans 12, 1 we read, do not be conformed to this world but be transformed by the renewing of your minds.

418
00:28:22.000 --> 00:28:26.000
In Psalm 1, our opening scripture, you can look at it there.

419
00:28:26.000 --> 00:28:29.000
It's laid before us those two paths of life.

420
00:28:29.000 --> 00:28:31.000
But where does it all begin?

421
00:28:31.000 --> 00:28:37.000
It begins by we're not listening to the counsel of the ungodly and walking according to that.

422
00:28:37.000 --> 00:28:39.000
Rather we're delighting in the law of the Lord.

423
00:28:39.000 --> 00:28:41.000
We're listening to God.

424
00:28:41.000 --> 00:28:43.000
So what are we listening to?

425
00:28:43.000 --> 00:28:45.000
What is shaping our minds?

426
00:28:45.000 --> 00:28:54.000
Last week I heard about studies that show the influence of what we listen to at the last part of our day

427
00:28:54.000 --> 00:28:59.000
and the first part of our day can have on our minds and our emotions.

428
00:28:59.000 --> 00:29:05.000
As we sleep and as we wake, like what's set in the trajectory for the day.

429
00:29:05.000 --> 00:29:15.000
And to then hear that and think, well, is it a great pattern of renewing our minds by ending the day,

430
00:29:15.000 --> 00:29:25.000
cuddling up with Netflix and waking first thing in the day and grabbing for the phone and going right into email or whatever it is.

431
00:29:25.000 --> 00:29:30.000
What is going to renew our minds?

432
00:29:30.000 --> 00:29:36.000
All the while as we're hearing all these different voices and we're hearing what's happening in the world around us,

433
00:29:36.000 --> 00:29:46.000
Christ is present and inviting us to be with Him, to hear Him, to speak with Him in prayer, to hear His voice in His Word.

434
00:29:46.000 --> 00:29:52.000
And that's true both in those quiet times with Him when we're cutting off the other voices.

435
00:29:52.000 --> 00:29:57.000
But it's also true that He's present with us throughout the day, calling us to walk with Him.

436
00:29:57.000 --> 00:30:03.000
So it speaks of the renewing of our minds, what are we filling our minds with, what's shaping our thoughts.

437
00:30:03.000 --> 00:30:07.000
But then we also see it leads to the transformation of our lives.

438
00:30:07.000 --> 00:30:11.000
As our minds are renewed, our lives are transformed.

439
00:30:11.000 --> 00:30:17.000
In 2 Corinthians chapter 3, verse 18, we see there that the more we see of Jesus in His Word,

440
00:30:17.000 --> 00:30:26.000
the more we are going to reflect His lightness in our lives.

441
00:30:26.000 --> 00:30:35.000
So this Christ is with us throughout all of life in every decision we face, patiently teaching us and helping us to follow Him.

442
00:30:35.000 --> 00:30:40.000
The Spirit of God is at work, wanting to transform us into His lightness.

443
00:30:40.000 --> 00:30:45.000
So the question is, will we follow Him?

444
00:30:45.000 --> 00:30:48.000
Have we put off the old self and put on the new self?

445
00:30:48.000 --> 00:30:55.000
And then are we looking to Him that we might live out of this new self, live this life He has given us?

446
00:30:55.000 --> 00:30:59.000
Let's pray.

447
00:30:59.000 --> 00:31:08.000
God, I pray that even now we would know Your presence with us here in this stillness.

448
00:31:08.000 --> 00:31:16.000
Lord, I pray that if there are those here who still only have that old self who are in need of this new self,

449
00:31:16.000 --> 00:31:24.000
Lord, I pray that they would receive Christ by faith, that they would put off the old self and receive the new self,

450
00:31:24.000 --> 00:31:29.000
that they would receive the life of Jesus.

451
00:31:29.000 --> 00:31:35.000
Lord, for those who are needing to be renewed and transformed,

452
00:31:35.000 --> 00:31:43.000
Lord, I pray that we too would hear Christ's invitation to come to Him and to learn of Him.

453
00:31:43.000 --> 00:31:48.000
Lord, make Your presence known to us both now and this moment.

454
00:31:48.000 --> 00:31:54.000
Shape us into Your lightness in the weeks and months and years to come.

455
00:31:54.000 --> 00:31:59.000
Before we sing, I'd like for us to just spend a moment with the Lord in prayer.

456
00:31:59.000 --> 00:32:04.000
So whatever He's speaking to you about, come to Him in prayer.

457
00:32:04.000 --> 00:32:08.000
Commit that to Him. Let's pray.

